    <stitle>STEERING GENERAL SERVICE INFORMATION AND FRONT WHEEL ALIGNMENT - ALIGNMENT SPECIFICATIONS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>ALIGNMENT SPECIFICATIONS</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="align" graphiccount="0">
            <title>ALIGNMENT PROCEDURE RULES</title>
            <para>When performing front wheel alignment procedures, observe the following rules:</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Caster angles are for an unladen (no payload) vehicle. If frame is not level, the frame
                    angle must be added to - front low - or subtracted from - front high - the caster angle to obtain
                    true caster reading. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s02001k_14.xml" xrefid="hl0200106">Adjusting For Frame Angle</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Caster angle difference between left and right wheel not to exceed one (1) degree.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Toe-in dimension may be measured from center of tread, or from inside of tire.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tolerance unless otherwise noted:</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Caster - plus or minus &#189; (.5) degree.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Toe-in - plus or minus 1/16 inch (1.59 mm).</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Camber - plus or minus 7/16 degree.</para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Axle manufacturers do not recommend bending axles to change camber angles.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
